1. Filesystem expansion-:

df -Th   ---- to see available size on filesystem and also type of filesystem
lsblk -f   ----- to see filesystem and mounpoint

sudo growpart /dev/nvme0n1 3   ===== expand partition
sudo xfs_growfs /    ==== expand XFS filesystem
sudo resize2fs /dev/nvme0n1p3      ===== expand ext4 filesystem

df -Th   ==== to verify filesystem is expanded or not


/dev is a special directory in Linux that contains device files.




create new partition and new filesystem from existing disk-:
expand ebs volume first in aws console.
1. [root@ip-172-31-79-146 ec2-user]# lsblk
2. [root@ip-172-31-79-146 ec2-user]# sudo fdisk /dev/nvme0n1

